What is RDS?
Managed relational database service.

AWS handles:
Backups
Patching
Monitoring
Failover

Supported Databases:
MySQL
PostgreSQL
MariaDB
Oracle
SQL Server

Architecture:
Application
     ↓
Primary DB
     ↓
Standby DB

Multi-AZ:
Database replicated to another AZ.

If primary fails:

Primary Down
     ↓
Automatic Failover
     ↓
Standby Becomes Primary

Read Replica:
Used for read-heavy workloads.

Primary DB
   │
   ├── Read Replica
   ├── Read Replica
   └── Read Replica

Real-Time Scenario:
Online Shopping Website

Users
  ↓
Application
  ↓
RDS MySQL

Stores:

Orders
Customers
Payments
